					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-gears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172464); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=172464&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251208" alt="Dr Gears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=172464)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-gears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172464); return false;" >Dr Gears</a></span> <span class="odate time_1232381179 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Jan 2009 16:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-360685">
									

<p>My objection is to the PDA's being unchanged except for new data-type SCP being on them. SCP-914 is very random, and i think the chances of it leaving the physical make-up unchanged every time is astronomically low. Possibly one test would result in a new device containing or emitting a data-type SCP, but i think the others would be random changes.</p>

