					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kaos-machina" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(264899); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=264899&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251208" alt="Kaos Machina" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=264899)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kaos-machina" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(264899); return false;" >Kaos Machina</a></span> <span class="odate time_1232393573 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Jan 2009 19:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-360907">
									

<p>Gears: Thanks for pointing that out, and you've just given me a new idea or three- after all, if it reacts strangely to <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/SCP-808" onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank'); return false;">SCP-808</a>, who's to say that it might not have similarly strange reactions to other SCPs?<br />
Then I thought, what would happen if you put one of these 317-containing PDAs into 914-<em>with 808 there?</em> What would happen to 317 as a result?<br />
But as for your concern, I did realize you were right, and I am putting a note in there that points out the strangeness of this, as well as putting another test in there that ends very strangely.</p>
<p>Scrat: The way I see it, while it certainly has some traits in common with a virus, so does 317. And on that note, it seems to me that they both have more in common with an AI program. I believe that 732 is more of an out of control program that spreads like a virus, yet otherwise seems to be an AI gone mad- but that's just my opinion, hindered by the fact that I generally suck with words. I would like to hear what others think on the subject, as well.</p>

							</div>

								
					
